22/08/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- A Montenegrin official was quoted as saying on Thursday (21 August) that only the five leading aluminum producers in the world would be allowed to compete in the sale of the state-run Kombinat Aluminijuma Podgorica (KAP) plant. 
Mihailo Banjevic, KAP's chief executive officer, added that the plant should go for about 238m euros. 
The buyer would also have to pay the company's debt of 285m euros. 
(Reuters - 21/08/03)
